jakosc writes "The Economist has an interesting article about increasing
the efficiency of wind-powered generators by turning them into [0]flying
wind farms. These tethered generators would harness high speed jet stream
winds above 15,000 ft and [1]in theory could give outputs of 40MW per
generator. (links to a pdf) The developer's website has [2]more details
of some of the safety, technological and economic issues."

