| New Laws of Robotics Proposed for US Kill-Bots                     |
|   from the maybe-calling-them-kill-bots-is-a-bad-first-step dept.  |
|   posted by Zonk on Saturday April 14, @16:43 (Sci-Fi)             |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/14/1718241     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jakosc writes "The Register has a short commentary about [0]a proposed
new set of laws of robotics for war robots by John S Canning of the Naval
Surface Warfare Centre. Unlike [1]Azimov's three laws of robotics Canning
[2]proposes (pdf) that we should 'Let machines target other machines and
let men target men.' Although this sounds OK in principle, 'a robot could
decide under Mr Canning's rules, to target a weapon system such as an
AK47 for destruction on its own initiative, requiring no permission from
a human. If the person holding it was thereby killed, that would be
collateral damage and the killer droid would be in the clear.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://politics.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/14/1718241

Links:
    0. http://www.theregister.co.uk/2007/04/13/i_robowarrior/
    1. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_robotics
    2. http://www.dtic.mil/ndia/2006disruptive_tech/canning.pdf


